<a id="top"> </a><h1>Tenure-track Position, Howard University</h1>
<p>
Department of Philosophy invites applications for one tenure-track 
position at the rank of assistant professor for the fall of 2012, 
pending the approval of funding. AOS: Philosophy of Science. AOC: Open, 
but the department has special needs in the following areas: Logic, 
History of Analytic Philosophy, and Neuroscience. Candidates must have a 
Ph.D. in Philosophy and be willing to explore areas of philosophical 
scholarship beyond the traditions of Western Philosophy. Successful 
candidates will be expected to teach both undergraduate and graduate 
courses as well as supervise graduate theses, and perform normal 
non-teaching duties. A complete application must include a cover letter, 
stating current interests, a CV, evidence of teaching excellence, three 
current letters of reference and one writing sample. Please send 
applications to: 
